worth the trouble generally to specifically raise a stat)<br><br>*IF* your buffed AC &gt; 1300, then your priorities would fall something more like this...<br><br>1.  Haste (Up to 34%)<br>2.  HP/Stamina<br>3.  Regen/Haste (Above 34%)<br>4.  Resists<br>5.  AC<br>6.  Other Stats<br><br>Basically, the reasoning here is that for all intensive purposes, AC above 1300 will give you only nominal benefits.  This has been parsed right up to the 1800 range given the existing mobs in game.  This *might* change in POP.<br><br>Also, I note the 34% is the point where haste becomes a low priority issue.  The reasoning is this... monks at 60 are capped to a maximum of 100% haste, at level 59 the cap is 80% haste.  (Yeah, you could argue it's 105, but Imho, the 105 figure is based on bad rounding of the parses).  So, what that means is that with Shissar (66% haste) + 34% haste item, you *will* reach your haste cap at level 60.  So basically, in a raid scenario, haste above 34% is gravy.<br><br>So why would you get any haste item above 34%?  Well, there are times you won't have spell haste such as when you're dispelled, no chanter, or soloing... in those cases, the extra haste will benefit you significantly.  Also, there are mobs who will slow you (overwrite the haste component of any spells on you), in those cases higher base item haste will also help you.<br><br>LaotzuQigong<br>60 Grandmaster<br>Legendary<br>The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uharbromme.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harbromme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 346<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 6:09:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 belts...</span><hr size=1> Yuffie, if your priorities are on no drop stuff the decision is even easier as the PoA belts are no drop, spider fur is not